Other observations: On days we do our water sampling and D.O. readings- we have seen mallards and ducklings- loons and babies in Turner and Pike Lakes- as well as huge flocks of Canadian geese with goslings- blue herons- and bald eagles. On July 15th- we saw an otter just beyond my pier on Pike Lake. It was the first otter seen in 3 or 4 years.
